<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/46920502-tara"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1506707450i/46920502._UX100_CR0,18,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/46920502-tara">Tara </a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    The only rationale that I could conceive was to create a dividing line between who could possibly be the copycat killer depending whether or not they <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    The only rationale that I could conceive was to create a dividing line between who could possibly be the copycat killer depending whether or not they knew the Whistler had been killed prior to Hillary Robart's murder. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
