  <span id="freeText14622121990253092614" style="display:none">A serial killer has been murdering women...but is he murdering all the women who have been murdered? It's not Dalgleish's case, but he's caught up in it anyay...<br /><br />Not my favorite of her books. It feels like a lot of extra busywork and complexity has been added in order to muck up the reader's ability to solve the case. A lot of social stuff about nuclear power plants that's more legerdemain than anything else. Aaaaand most of this doesn't focus on Dalgleish, and his "replacement" isn't nearly as engaging a character.<br /><br />Still lots better than a poke in the eye with a sharp book.</span>
